title: N.Y. Comp. Codes R. & Regs. Tit. 12 §§ 186-7.1 - Contracts with more stringent requirements
content:
N.Y. Comp. Codes R. & Regs. Tit. 12 §§ 186-7.1 - Contracts with more stringent requirements

State Regulations

Nothing in this Part shall prevent the employer of a
child performer from complying with a collective bargaining agreement or other
contract that establishes more stringent standards than those contained in this

Part. Notes
N.Y. Comp. Codes R. & Regs. Tit. 12
§§
186-7.1

State regulations are updated quarterly; we currently have two versions available. Below is a
comparison between our most recent version and the prior quarterly release. More comparison features will be added as we have more versions to compare. No prior version found.
